N2  - This paper gives a necessary and sufficient condition for the following proposition, in which ? and ?i for i = 1,?, n are weak orders on a finite set X. There are real-valued functions f1, f2,?, fn on X such that, for all x and y in X and i in {1,?,n}x?i y if and only if fi(x) ≤ fi(y), and x ? y if and only if fl(x) + ? + fn(x) ≤ fl(y) + ? + fn(y). The condition can be viewed as an extension of a simple unanimity or dominance condition.
